<text>Mouse cursor

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

The cursor commands allow you to change the mouse cursor to an image located by the specified file name or URL (the first command in the following), or to an image provided by the system (the second command in the following). The third command clears the cursor.

Syntax:

cursor [file name or address] ([x], [y])
cursor [cursor constant]
cursor null

The x and y parameters specify the coordinate of the hot spot, relative to the upper-left corner of the image. The ideal size of the cursor image, by default, is 32x32 on Windows. The available cursor constants are: CROSSHAIR_CURSOR, DEFAULT_CURSOR, E_RESIZE_CURSOR, HAND_CURSOR, MOVE_CURSOR, N_RESIZE_CURSOR, NE_RESIZE_CURSOR, NW_RESIZE_CURSOR, S_RESIZE_CURSOR, SE_RESIZE_CURSOR, SW_RESIZE_CURSOR, TEXT_CURSOR, W_RESIZE_CURSOR, and WAIT_CURSOR.

   
    

